            <div type="apparatus" resp="#JP">
                <listApp>
                    <app loc="Line 4">
                        <note>Alessi reported the text as intact and read MELANTHI· ; the text seems to have suffered damaged to the right margin since discovery</note>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="Line 4-5"><note>Mommsen suggested 'potius Melanth(e) in suo, quam Melanthin(a) suo'.</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Sacred to the shades of the underworld. Lurius Zosimus lived for 7 years. Luria Melanthin made it for her son.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en" resp="#LT">
                <p>The reading Melanthin, based on Alessi's text is acceptable as
                    it is: this is the Latin transliteration of the Greek name Μελάνθιν, a
                    "shortened" diminutive of Μελανθώ (via Μελάνθιον); this type of
                    "shortening" in -ιον and -ιος endings (the exact nature of which, whether phonetic or
                    morphological, is debated) occurs very frequently in inscriptions
                    and papyri of the Roman period. The form
                    Μελάνθιν is attested once in a third-century AD Macedonian inscription
                    (IG 10.2,1 204), whereas LGPN has 4 attestations of Μελανθώ dating to
                    the Hellenistic period.</p>
            </div>
